.TH SPIT "1" "January 2026" "GNU gettext-tools 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
spit \- translate some text through a Large Language Model
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spit
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Passes standard input to a Large Language Model (LLM) instance and prints
the response.
With the \fB\-\-to\fR option, it translates standard input to the specified language
through a Large Language Model (LLM) and prints the translation.
.PP
Warning: The output might not be what you expect.
It might be of the wrong form, be of poor quality, or reflect some biases.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-species\fR=\fI\,TYPE\/\fR
Specifies the type of LLM.  The default and only
valid value is 'ollama'.
.TP
\fB\-\-url\fR=\fI\,URL\/\fR
Specifies the URL of the server that runs the LLM.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR=\fI\,MODEL\/\fR
Specifies the model to use.
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR=\fI\,LANGUAGE\/\fR
Specifies the target language.
.TP
\fB\-\-prompt\fR=\fI\,TEXT\/\fR
Specifies the prompt to use before standard input.
This option overrides the \fB\-\-to\fR option.
.TP
\fB\-\-postprocess\fR=\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR
Specifies a command to post\-process the output.
.PP
Informative output:
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display this help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Output version information and exit.
